India’s Singh to Review Disaster Preparedness, Press Trust Says

-- B y   K a r t i k a y   M e h r o t r a
-- 
2011-06-01T04:23:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/india-s-singh-to-review-disaster-preparedness-press-trust-says.html
Prime Minister  Manmohan Singh  will
today review India’s disaster preparedness following the nuclear
crisis in Japan, the Press Trust of India reported, citing
unidentified people.  Among steps to be considered is the installation of
equipment to monitor and measure levels of radiation in 35
cities, according to the report.  Singh will assess nuclear safety issues overseen by the
Atomic Energy Regulatory Board and the Department of Atomic
Energy, Press Trust said.  -- Editors: John Chacko, Ryan Woo  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kartikay Mehrotra in  New Delhi  at 
 kmehrotra2@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
